{
  "text": "The SILS is a brief, self-administered test of general intellectual functioning in adolescents and adults [CITATION_1] . It consists of two subtests that measure vocabulary and abstract reasoning, and full-scale Wechsler Adult Intelligence ScaleRevised: 2006; [CITATION_2] ) and relies more on prefrontal function than the vocabulary subtest, which is an indicator of crystallized intelligence [CITATION_3] .",
